article.description: Cappie Pondexter's second-half scoring spree carried Rutgers past pesky Western Kentucky.
article.headline: Pondexter leads Rutgers' late charge
article.linkText: Rutgers runs wild in the second half
article.story:
ATHENS, Ga. (AP) -- Cappie Pondexter scored 13 of her 21 points
in the last 11 minutes, and Rutgers overcame an eight-minute
scoreless drought in the second half to beat Western Kentucky 64-52
in the first round of the NCAA women's Midwest Regional on
Saturday.

	   Pondexter added 10 rebounds, five assists and six steals, and
Chelsea Newton scored 14 points for fourth-seeded Rutgers (21-7).

	   The Scarlet Knights will face the winner of the
Georgia-Charlotte game on Monday.

	   Leslie Logsdon scored 13 points for Western Kentucky (22-9).

	   Western Kentucky overcame a 31-23 halftime deficit by scoring 11
straight points early in the second half. Rutgers countered with an
11-0 run and scored 11 unanswered points later in the half to help
clinch the win.

	   Rutgers was held to three points the first nine minutes of the
second half. After Michelle Campbell scored inside with 18:40 left
to give Rutgers a 34-25 lead, the Scarlet Knights didn't score
again until Pondexter's basket with 10:53 remaining.

	   Rutgers' press forced 12 second-half turnovers by Western
Kentucky.
